cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.AR, cs.PL

This paper discusses a security threat related to Intel SGX, which is a hardware-based security feature. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the practical implementation of enclave malware, which involves software engineering and system design, making cs.SE (Software Engineering) a likely category as well. The paper also involves low-level system details and hardware architecture, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.AR (Architecture) possible categories. Finally, the paper involves the use of code-reuse attacks, which is a topic related to programming languages, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) a possible category as well.
